The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to the distribution of points in high-dimensional spaces. This suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of discrepancy measures and epsilon-nets suggests a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), while the use of optimization techniques and approximation algorithms suggests a connection to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
